reviewText:
Early Access Review

For a game that is still on Alpha, it successfully manages to hook players in for a long period of time despite its early content and diversity.

A game that despite its current early stage is already fully capable of projecting an enchanting medieval atmosphere throughout the entire game play either on its singleplayer or in real time multiplayer battles.
Kingdom Wars 2: Battles can be seen as a huge improvement from similar game series such as The Settlers, that is also capable of defining with accuracy the true way of RTS games genre.

The pros of this game:
Charming and wonderful graphics that makes players feel an unique medieval atmosphere in it;

A game that shows a lot of diversity so far despite its short variety available (which is understandable considering that this game is still on Alpha);

Both game mechanics as well the user interface are simple and good looking;

A crafting system that makes this game different from the usual RTS games genre;

Good music selection that contributes to the medieval atmosphere this game has to offer visually;

And last but not least, the first impression that I obtained after playing this game is that it has a bright and promising future ahead of it!


The cons of this game:
Lack of players; (This isn't exactly a con because with the excellency of a game like Kingdom Wars 2: Battles gives to players, it does deserve a LOT more players playing it).

The game currently has bugs and lack of content that can give your opponent serious advantage over you, but such things will eventually be fixed through patches;

Unstable multiplayer mode with usual de-syncs and some lag spikes from time to time.

Conclusion
My conclusion on this game is a bit hard to determinate because it is far from finished, but one thing I can guarantee, that this game has potential and a promising future ahead of it!

This game has the nice concept of adding zombies into a RTS as an added treath to manage as you fight against your enemy. The greatest problems is that it fails on everything else. Here my Pro/Cons list.

~Pros:
∎ Zombies will rise from dead bodies, trying to kill everything comes near, they will siege castles and swarm and block some paths, requiring to add new strategies constantly as the battle on the field evolves;
∎ Three factions with detailed and big unlock trees that makes possible to customize your army with different kind of units;
∎ Survival mode: zombies will rise and attack you in waves, each wave bigger and stronger.

~Cons:
∎ Poor and low aestethically interface with a poor trade" function (you can trade crafting materials with other players) where it's not that clear who is buying what and for how much. Luckily I didn't fall in that but have seen lots of people trying to exchange 'a golden palace for a few copper coins';
∎ FPS drops even on high end computers (probably no problems on the last two models of nvidia) when you select units
